  "answer": "C) 14. C: Cerebral perfusion pressure CPP = MAP − Intracranial pressure (ICP). Under normal circumstances of a MAP between 60 and 160 mmHg and ICP about 10 mmHg (CPP of 50–150 mmHg) sufficient blood flow can be maintained with autoregulation.",
  "chapter": "General Surgery",
