  "answer": "E) 17. E: Nickel Cancer of the nasal cavity is associated with many carcinogenic materials including nickel dust. Other carcinogens are listed in the following: • Human papillomavirus (HPV) • Specific inhalants including dust from the wood, textiles, or leather industries, flour dust, nickel dust, chromium dust, mustard gas, asbestos, fumes from rubbing alcohol (isopropyl alcohol), radium fumes, glue fumes, formaldehyde fumes, and solvent fumes used in furniture and shoe production • Air pollution • Marijuana use",
  "chapter": "General Surgery",
