  "answer": "A) 18. A: Aniline dyes Transitional cell carcinoma of the urinary tract is associated with cigarette smok-ing, which contributes to approximately one-half of the disease burden. Chemical exposure including petroleum, paints, and pigments (e.g., aniline dyes) is known to predispose to this disease. As with most epithelial cancers, physical irritation has also been associated with increased risk of malignant transformation (e.g., chronic urinary stones, chronic catheterization, and chronic infections).",
