  "answer": "C) 32. C: Coeliac trunk The coeliac trunk is closely related to the fibres of the greater splanchnic nerves (Figure 1). Inferior gastroepiploic Proper hepatic phrenic Gastroduodenal Common Right gastric hepatic Superior Right MiddleInferior pancreaticoduodenal colic colic pancreaticoduodenal Ileocolic artery mesenteric artery T12 Coeliac trunk Left gastric L1 Inferior suprarenal Renal arteries L2 Gonadal arteries Oesophageal branches Splenic artery Short gastric arteries Left gastroepiploic Ileal arteries Jejunial arteries Inferior Left mesenteric artery Sigmoid branches Lumbar arteries L4 Comon lliac Superior rectal Figure 1 The abdominal aorta including the coeliac axis, SMA, and IMA.",
