  "answer": "E) 38. E: Immunoglobulin G Type III hypersensitivity reaction occurs when there is accumulation of immune complexes (antigen-antibody complexes) that have not been adequately cleared by innate immune cells, giving rise to an inflammatory response and activation of leukocytes. Such reactions result in immune complex diseases. Antibody (IgG) binds to soluble antigen, forming a circulating immune com-plex. Examples include systemic lupus erythematosus (SLE) and rheumatoid arthritis (RA).",
