  "answer": "D) 43. D: Indirect inguinal hernia There is a positive cough impulse suggestive of bowel herniation. The doctor cannot get above the lump, suggesting that it arises from the inguinal canal. The hernia can be reduced back along the inguinal canal from the scrotum and upon occlusion of the deep inguinal ring the hernia is controlled. This is pathognomonic for an indirect inguinal hernia.",
