  "question": "A 32-year-old man presents complaining of a ‘dragging’ sensation in the left scrotum. On examination, the doctor can palpate a soft mass which feels like a ‘bag of worms’ but only when the patient is standing. Diagnosis? A Testicular cancer B Testicular torsion C Direct inguinal hernia D Indirect inguinal hernia E Varicocele",
