  "question": "A 67-year-old woman suffers from rheumatoid arthritis which affects both hips. She falls when walking back from town. Her plain X-ray reveals an intracapsular fracture of the femoral neck. Select the operation you would recommend: A Dynamic hip screw B Cannulated screws C Uncemented hemiarthroplasty D Cemented hemiarthroplasty E Total hip replacement",
