  "question": "A 35-year-old woman is hit by a car. The plain X-ray shows an intracapsular fracture of the right femoral neck. Select the operation you would recommend. A Traction B Dynamic hip screw C Cannulated screws D Intramedullary hip screw E Hemiarthroplasty",
