  "answer": "A) 64. A: Prolactin The anterior pituitary gland (adenohypophysis or pars distalis) synthesizes and secretes the following six hormones: follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH), luteinizing hormone (LH), growth hormone, prolactin, ACTH, and thyroid-stimulating hormone (TSH). The posterior pituitary gland (neurohypophysis) produces only two hormones: ADH (also known as vasopressin) and oxytocin. These hormones are synthesized by the hypothalamus and then stored and secreted by the posterior pituitary gland into the bloodstream.",
  "chapter": "General Surgery",
