  "question": "A 22-year-old man is brought into the emergency department following a road traffic accident. He sustained an open fracture of the right tibia and fibula. His HR is 110 bpm, blood pressure (BP) 108/85, respiratory rate (RR) 28, urine output is 30 mL in the last hour. Which class of haemorrhagic shock does he fall into?",
