  "answer": "D) 189. D: Clostridium perfringens Gas gangrene is a form of spreading tissue necrosis that occurs when spores of Clostridia perfringens infect wounds with extensive soft tissue or muscle injury. Palpable crepitus and gas shadows on radiographs may be noted. Prompt diag-nosis and definitive treatment with debridement of necrotic tissues, intravenous antibiotics, and supportive care such as hyperbaric oxygen therapy, are vital to prevent poor outcome.",
