  "answer": "C) 193. C: Osteosarcoma Papillary and follicular carcinomas of thyroid respond to growth-promoting effects of TSH. Oestrogens are associated with breast and endometrial carcino-mas. Oestrogen receptor-modulating drug (tamoxifen) is used to blockade the oestrogen receptors in breast carcinoma. Prostatic epithelium and carcinomas are dependent upon androgenic stimulation for growth and survival.",
  "chapter": "General Surgery",
