  "answer": "C) 197. C: Mycoplasma arthritis Primary antibody deficiency (PAD) syndromes are disorders of B-cell develop-ment or function with impaired or absent antibody production. A PAD presents with pneumonia, sinus, and gastrointestinal infections because of the absence of immunoglobulin G (IgG) and immunoglobulin A (IgA). PAD patients with low IgG levels are susceptible to Mycoplasma arthritis. It results in joint destruction and chronic pain. Treatment is with a combination of surgery and tetracycline.",
  "chapter": "General Surgery",
