  "answer": "B) 199. B: Papillary thyroid carcinoma Psammoma bodies are concentric calcified structures that are a pathognomic feature of papillary carcinoma of thyroid. They are usually present in the cores of the papillae but may also be noted in draining lymph nodes and adjacent tis-sues. They may also be found in meningiomas and pituitary prolactinomas.",
