  "question": "An 83-year-old man has chest pain, breathlessness, and ankle oedema. On clinical examination, cardiomegaly is identified and a subsequent diagnosis of viral myocarditis is made. Which of the following microorganisms is most likely responsible for this illness: A Rhinovirus B Mumps C Coronavirus D Adenovirus E Coxsackie B",
