  "question": "Which of the following regarding the coronary arteries is correct:\nA The sinoatrial node is supplied by the left coronary artery in most cases\nB The atrioventricular node is supplied by the left coronary artery in most cases\nC The circumflex artery is a branch of the right coronary artery\nD Occlusion of the anterior inter-ventricular artery (left anterior descending artery) results in an anterior myocardial infarction\nE Angina is always due to athero-sclerosis of the coronary vessels",
