  "answer": "C) Buccinator is a muscle of facial expression and is therefore innervated by the facial nerve. The lateral pterygoid, masseter, anterior belly of digastric, and temporalis are all muscles of mastication and therefore innervated by the mandibular division of the trigeminal nerve (Vc).",
