  "answer": "E) E: It has a peak hormonal concentration in the morning\nCortisol is a steroid hormone that is released in stress to cause an increase in blood glucose. It is a catabolic hormone. It is stimulated by ACTH released from the anterior pituitary. ACTH is stimulated by CRH released from the median eminence of the hypothalamus. It has a diurnal variation and peaks on wak-ing up in the morning. Its lowest level is around midnight and this is why a ‘midnight cortisol’ is used to detect excess cortisol production in Cushing’s syndrome.",
  "chapter": "General Surgery",
